Amalfitano et al., J. Virol. 72:926 (1998
)). By deleting the entire adenovirus genome, very large inserts of heterologous DNA can be accommodated. Generation of so called "gutless" adenoviruses, where all viral genes are deleted, are particularly advantageous for insertion of large inserts of heterologous DNA (for a review, see 
Yeh. and Perricaudet, FASEB J. 11:615 (1997
)).






